programme.desc: Who is the bloody figure wielding a meat cleaver, seen racing through the alleys of British Columbia’s Chinatown? Whoever he is, he has terrified dozens of witnesses, who have never been the same afterwards. The brutal history of Cornwall Jail, Ottawa’s most notorious prison, lives on as ghostly apparitions of tortured inmates terrorize modern visitors. In its heyday it was home to vicious criminals, and sadistic guards. Hangings, whippings and torture were daily affairs and spirits from that era still linger on in the maze of cell blocks and corridors. Many male criminals were hanged at the Northwest Mounted Police outpost known as Fort Saskatchewan, but only one woman. Florence Lassandro was dubbed the Mob Princess, and her spirit is one of many seen on the grounds and in the preserved buildings of this historic site. Journey through several of the world's most haunted prisons and experience real portals to hell on earth.

Breaking down barriers of expression and social mores, the Decline punks were against everything: They gave birth to an anti-establishment view of the world that permeates today's music, politics, social attitudes, styles and trends. The film documents their deliberate reaction to the mass commercialism of music; it is a blatant and angry rejection of the mainstream. programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: Surviving Mann returns with its most punishing season opener yet. In true Don Mann fashion, the bar is raised with a grueling 10-part physical readiness test—infused with a blast of hypothermia for good measure. Don himself calls it “the most brutal PT [he’s] ever witnessed,” and it’s clear the contestants are in for a world of hurt. To push them even further, MMA legend Ken Shamrock joins the fray, bringing his no-nonsense intensity to whip the group into fighting shape. Those who survive the trial by ice and exertion are rewarded with a chance to test-fire the lightest AR on the market—if they can still feel their trigger fingers.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: For the first time in Surviving Mann history, the contestants undergo intense combat training led by none other than Ken Shamrock—"the most dangerous man in the world." His relentless situation drills push this elite group beyond their limits, sharpening their instincts and forging next-level tactical readiness. As a new mission begins to take shape, the pressure mounts—and the team learns that the strongest among them will earn a game-changing reward. But in a world where every edge matters, not everyone is built to keep up. Fatigue sets in, tensions rise, and the difference between teammate and competitor begins to blur. With Shamrock watching closely, only the most disciplined will rise to meet the challenge—and prove they’re worthy of what lies ahead.

programme.title: Wild Shots
programme.desc: In this episode of Wildshots, host Tim Harmsen heads to Sig Sauer for an exclusive look inside one of America’s most advanced firearms manufacturing facilities. With a motto of “Every day you wake up and get a little better,” Sig Sauer lives up to its words—producing over 5,000 firearms a day with cutting-edge robotics and precision automation. After a full factory tour, Tim hits Sig’s state-of-the-art testing range to get hands-on with the legendary XM250 machine gun, pushing the limits of modern firepower. Then it’s time for some pure shooting mastery as Tim meets up with friend and firearms influencer 22Plinkster. Known for his unbelievable accuracy and showmanship, 22Plinkster ups the ante—splitting playing cards with a .22 bullet, upside down, and even splitting a single bullet mid-flight to hit two separate targets at once. Finally, the episode caps off with a nod to Hollywood as Tim checks out the Genesis Arms machinery seen in John Wick, blending cinematic cool with real-world firepower.

programme.title: Operation Dead Ringer: Busting Escobar's Cartel
programme.desc: Bill Gately and the U.S. Customs Service discover the owner of a coin laundry is laundering large sums of cash through a bank that originates from Columbia. Gately learns that one of the sources of the cash is none other than Pablo Escobar. Gately goes undercover and uses the man as a Trojan Horse to purchase one ton of cocaine, and follows the drugs to its destination. Along the way, the FBI bullies into the operation and loses the coke. Gately pulls out the stops to save his case and arrest those involved.

programme.title: Operation Wake Up Cafe: Illegal Betting In Jersey
programme.desc: Passaic County, New Jersey officer Julia Torres goes undercover to bust an illegal betting club entrenched in the Little Italy neighborhood. As a woman running the operation dominated by male wise guys, it's a constant juggling act to collect evidence while not being made as a cop. Along the way, Torres life-saving efforts on a small boy nearly expose her and the operation. She manages to record conversations and bring down the backroom gambling operation to the delight of neighbors who applaud her efforts.

programme.title: Operation Black Coral: Intercepting Caribbean Coke
programme.desc: Sarasota detective, Jim Sweeting, infiltrates the vicious Cuban cocaine pipeline controlled by the Medellin cartel. The agent re-invents himself and takes on an alias of a drug trafficker to collect evidence and break the back of the source. Along the way Sweeting enters a violent drugs and money world guided only by his wits and a trusted confidential informant. To bust the dealers and stay alive he must put in the performance of a lifetime or be exposed, and killed.

programme.title: Operation Dead Ringer: Busting Escobar's Cartel
programme.desc: Bill Gately and the U.S. Customs Service discover the owner of a coin laundry is laundering large sums of cash through a bank that originates from Columbia. Gately learns that one of the sources of the cash is none other than Pablo Escobar. Gately goes undercover and uses the man as a Trojan Horse to purchase one ton of cocaine, and follows the drugs to its destination. Along the way, the FBI bullies into the operation and loses the coke. Gately pulls out the stops to save his case and arrest those involved.

programme.title: Operation Wake Up Cafe: Illegal Betting In Jersey
programme.desc: Passaic County, New Jersey officer Julia Torres goes undercover to bust an illegal betting club entrenched in the Little Italy neighborhood. As a woman running the operation dominated by male wise guys, it's a constant juggling act to collect evidence while not being made as a cop. Along the way, Torres life-saving efforts on a small boy nearly expose her and the operation. She manages to record conversations and bring down the backroom gambling operation to the delight of neighbors who applaud her efforts.

programme.title: Operation Black Coral: Intercepting Caribbean Coke
programme.desc: Sarasota detective, Jim Sweeting, infiltrates the vicious Cuban cocaine pipeline controlled by the Medellin cartel. The agent re-invents himself and takes on an alias of a drug trafficker to collect evidence and break the back of the source. Along the way Sweeting enters a violent drugs and money world guided only by his wits and a trusted confidential informant. To bust the dealers and stay alive he must put in the performance of a lifetime or be exposed, and killed.

programme.title: Operation Dead Ringer: Busting Escobar's Cartel
programme.desc: Bill Gately and the U.S. Customs Service discover the owner of a coin laundry is laundering large sums of cash through a bank that originates from Columbia. Gately learns that one of the sources of the cash is none other than Pablo Escobar. Gately goes undercover and uses the man as a Trojan Horse to purchase one ton of cocaine, and follows the drugs to its destination. Along the way, the FBI bullies into the operation and loses the coke. Gately pulls out the stops to save his case and arrest those involved.

programme.title: Operation Wake Up Cafe: Illegal Betting In Jersey
programme.desc: Passaic County, New Jersey officer Julia Torres goes undercover to bust an illegal betting club entrenched in the Little Italy neighborhood. As a woman running the operation dominated by male wise guys, it's a constant juggling act to collect evidence while not being made as a cop. Along the way, Torres life-saving efforts on a small boy nearly expose her and the operation. She manages to record conversations and bring down the backroom gambling operation to the delight of neighbors who applaud her efforts.

programme.title: Operation Dead Ringer: Busting Escobar's Cartel
programme.desc: Bill Gately and the U.S. Customs Service discover the owner of a coin laundry is laundering large sums of cash through a bank that originates from Columbia. Gately learns that one of the sources of the cash is none other than Pablo Escobar. Gately goes undercover and uses the man as a Trojan Horse to purchase one ton of cocaine, and follows the drugs to its destination. Along the way, the FBI bullies into the operation and loses the coke. Gately pulls out the stops to save his case and arrest those involved.

programme.title: Operation Wake Up Cafe: Illegal Betting In Jersey
programme.desc: Passaic County, New Jersey officer Julia Torres goes undercover to bust an illegal betting club entrenched in the Little Italy neighborhood. As a woman running the operation dominated by male wise guys, it's a constant juggling act to collect evidence while not being made as a cop. Along the way, Torres life-saving efforts on a small boy nearly expose her and the operation. She manages to record conversations and bring down the backroom gambling operation to the delight of neighbors who applaud her efforts.
